1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:09,607
So basically, historically, Kafka depended on Apache ZooKeeper for cluster coordination — storing broker registrations, topic metadata, and controller election state.

2
00:00:09,557 --> 00:00:14,067
ZooKeeper is a separate distributed system with its own operational overhead.

3
00:00:14,067 --> 00:00:19,153
Here's something nobody tells you: most production bugs at FAANG aren't code bugs.

4
00:00:19,153 --> 00:00:21,163
They're system design bugs.

